**Practice Questions from PDFs:**

**Example 1: Democracy Passage (Lecture 5)**
Democracy should __(21)__ dignity of the individual. It should also aim at the __(22)__ good of the greatest __(23)__. The opposition party should __(24)__ the wrong plans, policies and decisions of the government in power. The government should cater to the __(25)__ needs of the people.

Answers: 21-ensure, 22-greatest, 23-number, 24-oppose, 25-genuine

