### 3. ERROR SPOTTING (8-10 questions expected)

**CRITICAL GRAMMAR RULES:**

#### Rule 1: Subject-Verb Agreement

**Concept: Fraction + of + Noun**
- One third of the work **has** been completed (work = singular)
- Half of the boys **have** been selected (boys = plural)

**Example from PDF:**
❌ One third of the house **were** divided
✅ One third of the house **was** divided

#### Rule 2: Between vs Among
- **Between** = Two persons/things
- **Among** = More than two

**Example:**
❌ Bilateral series between India, Pakistan and Sri Lanka
✅ Trilateral series among India, Pakistan and Sri Lanka

#### Rule 3: Comprises vs Comprises of
❌ This book comprises **of** 300 pages
✅ This book comprises 300 pages (no 'of')

#### Rule 4: Each Other vs One Another
- **Each other** = Two persons
- **One another** = More than two

**Example:**
❌ The two men were quarrelling with **one another**
✅ The two men were quarrelling with **each other**

#### Rule 5: Universal Truth (No Tense Change)
- He said that man **is** a social animal (not 'was')
- He said that the sun **rises** in the east (not 'rose')
- He said that plants **make** their own food (not 'made')

#### Rule 6: Unless (Negative + Positive)
❌ Unless you don't obey, you will not succeed
✅ Unless you obey, you will not succeed

#### Rule 7: Died of/from/for
- Died **of** = disease (He died of cancer)
- Died **for** = sacrifice (He died for his country)
- Died **from** = result (He died from overeating)
- Died **on** = hunger strike

#### Rule 8: Reason is 'that' (not 'because')
❌ The reason for his failure is **because** he didn't study
✅ The reason for his failure is **that** he didn't study

#### Rule 9: Few/Little + The
- I gave you **the few** pens **that** I had (specific)
- I gave you **a few** pens (some pens)
- **Little** knowledge he had proved helpful (not 'a little')

#### Rule 10: Inversion after Negative Words
❌ Never she visited there
✅ Never **did she visit** there

❌ Not a word she spoke
✅ Not a word **did she speak**

❌ Seldom or never my teacher **has taught** me
✅ Seldom or never **has my teacher taught** me

#### Rule 11: Who vs Whom
- **Who** = Subject (who will win)
- **Whom** = Object (whom I supported)

**Example:**
✅ Rahul is the candidate **who** will win
✅ This is the boy **whom** I have supported
✅ Rajat is the member **who**, I feel, will be selected

#### Rule 12: One of + Plural vs The only one of + Singular
- Rohit is **one of the players** that **have** scored
- Rohit is **the only one of the players** that **has** scored
- Mercury is **the only one of the metals** that **is** found in liquid state

#### Rule 13: Comparison (Different from, not 'than')
❌ Different **than**
✅ Different **from**

#### Rule 14: Reflexive Pronouns (Enjoy, Prepare, Qualify, Avail)
❌ I enjoyed **myself** at the party
✅ I enjoyed the party

❌ She prepared **herself** for the exam
✅ She prepared for the exam

✅ They qualified **themselves** in the exam (correct - need reflexive)
✅ He availed **himself** of every chance (correct - avail 'of' needs reflexive)

#### Rule 15: Stative Verbs (No Continuous Form)
**Stative Verbs:** have, own, possess, belong, know, understand, believe, love, hate, like, want, need, prefer, seem, appear, etc.

❌ He is **owning** two flats
✅ He **owns** two flats

❌ She is **having** many doubts
✅ She **has** many doubts

✅ She is having her dinner (correct - 'having' = eating here)

#### Rule 16: Adjectives (No -ly ending)
❌ He was a **coward** man
✅ He was a **cowardly** man

❌ She is a **miser** girl
✅ She is a **miserly** girl

